  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison refers to Oliver Johnson&apos;s letter and an undisclosed decision. Garrison writes: &quot;I think we have decided wisely, and that great and general relief will be experienced as soon as our announcement appears in print.&quot; Garrison seems to favor postponing certain anti-slavery meetings. They are not holding the New England Convention.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Includes an envelope with the delivery address: Oliver Johnson, Anti-Slavery Office, 5 Beekman Street, New York City.</subfield>
